reviews.review: Star Wars The Rise Of Skywalker is not everything it could have been but it still was an entertaining ride that had a lot of things to like about it.  It seemed like J.J. Abrams was picking up the pieces of The Last Jedi and bringing it closer to his original vision for the sequel trilogy and I have to say that I did not mind where Abrams took it.  Rise Of Skywalker is definitely better than Last Jedi but I still am trying to decide if I like Rise Of Skywalker better than Force Awakens.  I would say that the sequel trilogy is my least favorite of the three Star Wars trilogies; it did not seem to have a end goal, each episode just felt like it still did not know where the saga would end up.  The overall plot was very similar to my favorite Star Wars comic book called Dark Empire and that did enhance my enjoyment of this Star Wars film.  However The Rise Of Skywalker was a fun ride that had a lot of cool fan service that made me happy.
Just when I thought you couldn't get any dumber, you go and do something like this... and totally redeem yourself!
Better than the other two Disney Star Wars movies, which is not saying much.

Was it perfect?  No.  Go back and look at the originals/prequels.  Stop whining that you hate this movie.  It was great, fun and a fitting end to the saga I grew up watching for last 42 years.  Looking forward to more Star Wars movies/series in the future to enjoy with my kids.

I have only watched the movies and stories that have been released in theaters and have not read any Star Wars related books since the early 1990s nor have never read or watched any comics or other visual media. Only theatrical released movies, but many times! I thought it does a very good job of tying up numerous loose ends, bringing the past to a close while allowing for future movies that can still tie to the past.
